subSubSection.paragraph:
Nephthea laevis
; 
Roxas 1933
: 415; 
Verseveldt 1970
: 219, figs 5-6, pl. 3 fig. 1 (Gulf of Suez, Et Tur).

The polyps are up to about 0.7 mm high and 0.6 mm wide (Figure 37A). Supporting bundle not projecting, composed of spindles with simple tubercles, outer side and distal end with larger tubercles. Length of these spindles is up to 0.8 mm (Figure 37B). Polyp body sclerites irregularly arranged, the smallest are present adaxially; abaxially they merge into the smaller spindles of the supporting bundle (Figure 37C). The tentacle sclerites resemble the smallest adaxial polyp sclerites (Figures 37D, 39
B-C
).
